</h3><p class="sc-jUosCB eIJFN pf-45_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The pandemic has significantly impacted the mental health of parents and carers. The severity of the situation, emerging psychological issues, and limited access to mental health services have added to the challenges. Moreover, the cost of living crisis and concerns about digital harms have further increased anxiety and, in some cases, feelings of helplessness.
