</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-iCfMLu eehqFj pf-130_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-XxNYO eWQzGj pf-131_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cZMNgc bNHzPH pf-132_">Challenges faced by parents
</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Stem4_charity_s_impact_Fostering_family_resilience_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1708153900" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Stem4_charity_s_impact_Fostering_family_resilience_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1708153900 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Stem4_charity_s_impact_Fostering_family_resilience_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_1000x.png?v=1708153900 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Stem4_charity_s_impact_Fostering_family_resilience_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1708153900 320w" width="1440" height="960" alt="Stem4 charity's impact Fostering family resilience - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -.png__PID:4a9dbd85-1ddf-4e40-a017-1318c6812f41" title="Stem4 charity's impact: Fostering family resilience - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-134_"/><p class="sc-jUosCB eIJFN pf-135_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by JosieElias via Envato Elements</p><p class="sc-jUosCB eIJFN pf-137_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The pandemic has significantly impacted the mental health of parents and carers. The severity of the situation, emerging psychological issues, and limited access to mental health services have added to the challenges. Moreover, the cost of living crisis and concerns about digital harms have further increased anxiety and, in some cases, feelings of helplessness.
</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-iCfMLu eehqFj pf-139_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-XxNYO eWQzGj pf-140_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cZMNgc bNHzPH pf-141_">Creating positive relationships
</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Parental_wellbeing_essentials_A_guide_to_mental_health_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1708154030" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Parental_wellbeing_essentials_A_guide_to_mental_health_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1708154030 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Parental_wellbeing_essentials_A_guide_to_mental_health_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_1000x.png?v=1708154030 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Parental_wellbeing_essentials_A_guide_to_mental_health_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1708154030 320w" width="1451" height="968" alt="Parental wellbeing essentials A guide to mental health - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -.png__PID:e87ad855-3867-4c6b-bb70-dbaa062fee72" title="Parental wellbeing essentials: A guide to mental health - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-143_"/><p class="sc-jUosCB eIJFN pf-144_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by YuriArcursPeopleimages via Envato Elements</p><p class="sc-jUosCB eIJFN pf-146_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The theme for PMHD 2024, "Creating Positive Relationships," highlights the importance of healthy family dynamics. It's no secret that family relationships play a vital role in one's mental well-being. However, many parents and carers have reported a deterioration in their family's quality of life over the past year. They've experienced more arguments, less quality time together, and increased concerns about their family's mental health.
</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-iCfMLu eehqFj pf-148_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-XxNYO eWQzGj pf-149_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cZMNgc bNHzPH pf-150_">The role of relationships in wellbeing
</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Building_family_resilience_Stem4_s_positive_approach_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1708154191" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Building_family_resilience_Stem4_s_positive_approach_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1708154191 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Building_family_resilience_Stem4_s_positive_approach_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_1500x.png?v=1708154191 1280w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Building_family_resilience_Stem4_s_positive_approach_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_1000x.png?v=1708154191 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Building_family_resilience_Stem4_s_positive_approach_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1708154191 320w" width="1680" height="1121" alt="Building family resilience Stem4's positive approach - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -.png__PID:60c35ccc-5203-4f30-8fe3-febe9e853543" title="Building family resilience: Stem4's positive approach - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-152_"/><p class="sc-jUosCB eIJFN pf-153_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by Rawpixel via Envato Elements</p><p class="sc-jUosCB eIJFN pf-155_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Positive relationships contribute to happiness, warmth, and a sense of safety. They help individuals learn about themselves and build positive self-esteem. Being part of a supportive network enhances resilience and helps navigate life's challenges securely. Loneliness, on the other hand, is linked to mental health issues, including depression and anxiety.
</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-iCfMLu eehqFj pf-157_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-XxNYO eWQzGj pf-158_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cZMNgc bNHzPH pf-159_">Building strong relationships
</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Mental_health_awareness_PMHD_2024_perspectives_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1708154354" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Mental_health_awareness_PMHD_2024_perspectives_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1708154354 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Mental_health_awareness_PMHD_2024_perspectives_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_1500x.png?v=1708154354 1280w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Mental_health_awareness_PMHD_2024_perspectives_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_1000x.png?v=1708154354 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Mental_health_awareness_PMHD_2024_perspectives_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1708154354 320w" width="1613" height="1075" alt="Mental health awareness PMHD 2024 perspectives - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -.png__PID:3db13f91-382f-477d-90dc-299cd73954e1" title="Mental health awareness: PMHD 2024 perspectives - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-161_"/><p class="sc-jUosCB eIJFN pf-162_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by Rawpixel via Envato Elements</p><p class="sc-jUosCB eIJFN pf-164_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Building and maintaining positive relationships requires effort. It starts with self-acceptance and self-worth. Low self-esteem can lead to poor relationship choices, so working on self-positivity is crucial. Being clear about your relationship goals and values is essential. Effective communication, openness, and mutual respect are vital to successful relationships.
</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-iCfMLu eehqFj pf-166_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-XxNYO eWQzGj pf-167_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cZMNgc bNHzPH pf-168_">Parental involvement and support
</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Employee_support_in_focus_Parental_wellbeing_matters_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1708154449" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Employee_support_in_focus_Parental_wellbeing_matters_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1708154449 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Employee_support_in_focus_Parental_wellbeing_matters_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_1500x.png?v=1708154449 1280w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Employee_support_in_focus_Parental_wellbeing_matters_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_1000x.png?v=1708154449 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Employee_support_in_focus_Parental_wellbeing_matters_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1708154449 320w" width="1766" height="1179" alt="Employee support in focus Parental wellbeing matters - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -.png__PID:9050dac8-1e43-4a40-9d4d-ab4328a70da5" title="Employee support in focus: Parental wellbeing matters - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-170_"/><p class="sc-jUosCB eIJFN pf-171_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by YuriArcursPeopleimages via Envato Elements</p><p class="sc-jUosCB eIJFN pf-173_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Parent Mental Health Day encourages parents and carers to acknowledge their struggles, share their achievements, and learn how to connect positively with their families. It provides a platform to discuss parents' challenges and find ways to address them collectively.
</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-iCfMLu eehqFj pf-175_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-XxNYO eWQzGj pf-176_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cZMNgc bNHzPH pf-177_">How employers can support parental burnout
</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Workplace_wellbeing_strategies_Insights_from_PMHD_2024_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1708154584" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Workplace_wellbeing_strategies_Insights_from_PMHD_2024_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1708154584 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Workplace_wellbeing_strategies_Insights_from_PMHD_2024_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_1500x.png?v=1708154584 1280w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Workplace_wellbeing_strategies_Insights_from_PMHD_2024_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_1000x.png?v=1708154584 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Workplace_wellbeing_strategies_Insights_from_PMHD_2024_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1708154584 320w" width="1895" height="1285" alt="Workplace wellbeing strategies Insights from PMHD 2024 - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -.png__PID:51de3e4f-eef2-4f46-9c50-4f2608c96a78" title="Workplace wellbeing strategies: Insights from PMHD 2024 - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-179_"/><p class="sc-jUosCB eIJFN pf-180_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by zoranzeremski via Envato Elements</p><p class="sc-jUosCB eIJFN pf-182_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Parental burnout is a real concern, especially for working parents. The demands of work and family life can lead to stress and exhaustion. Employers must protect employees' health and well-being. Here are some ways employers can support parents facing burnout:
</p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-jHkVzv gbyaRg pf-184_"><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bQtKYq wvgEH pf-185_"><b>Good communication</b> - Encourage open conversations about mental health and offer flexible working options to help with childcare.
</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bQtKYq wvgEH pf-187_"><b>Regular check-ins</b> - Conduct regular one-to-one meetings with employees to identify signs of burnout early and provide support.
</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bQtKYq wvgEH pf-189_"><b>Promote an open culture</b> - Create a workplace culture where discussing mental health is as natural as discussing physical health.
</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bQtKYq wvgEH pf-191_"><b>Flexibility</b> - Be flexible in accommodating employees' needs, such as adjusting work hours or providing mentoring.
</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-iCfMLu eehqFj pf-193_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-XxNYO eWQzGj pf-194_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cZMNgc bNHzPH pf-195_">Conclusion</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/ComplyPlus_LMS_for_positive_family_dynamics_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1708154800" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/ComplyPlus_LMS_for_positive_family_dynamics_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1708154800 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/ComplyPlus_LMS_for_positive_family_dynamics_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_1500x.png?v=1708154800 1280w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/ComplyPlus_LMS_for_positive_family_dynamics_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_1000x.png?v=1708154800 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/ComplyPlus_LMS_for_positive_family_dynamics_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1708154800 320w" width="1728" height="1152" alt="ComplyPlus LMS™ for positive family dynamics - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -.png__PID:7f0b18fa-df69-4fcd-8d10-0803b26285ca" title="ComplyPlus LMS™ for positive family dynamics - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-197_"/><p class="sc-jUosCB eIJFN pf-198_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by milanzeremski via Envato Elements</p><p class="sc-jUosCB eIJFN pf-200_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">In conclusion, Parent Mental Health Day 2024 is a reminder of the importance of positive relationships within families. It's a day to acknowledge parents' challenges and seek support and understanding. Employers are crucial in supporting working parents' mental health, benefiting families and businesses. Let's all take a moment on January 27th to reflect on the balance in our lives and work towards creating positive relationships.<br><br>stem4 provides resources for young people to encourage good mental health, including apps and educational programs. They are dedicated to making a positive impact on the mental well-being of the youth.
<br><br>Remember, strong relationships are the foundation of a healthy, balanced life. Let's make Parent Mental Health Day 2024 a day of reflection, support, and positive change.
